<h2>Overview</h2>



The Comserv Mail System provides email functionality for users, including webmail access and email notifications. This guide explains how to use the mail features available to regular users.



<h2>Accessing Webmail</h2>



<h3>Step 1: Navigate to the Mail Page</h3>



<ol><li>Log in to your account</li></ol>

<ol><li>Click on the "Mail" link in the navigation menu</li></ol>

<ol><li>You will be directed to the mail page</li></ol>



<h3>Step 2: Access Your Webmail</h3>



<ol><li>On the mail page, you'll see a link to access webmail</li></ol>

<ol><li>Click on the "Mail" link</li></ol>

<ol><li>A new tab will open with the webmail interface</li></ol>

<ol><li>Enter your email credentials:</li></ol>

   - Username: your_username@[domain]

   - Password: your email password



<h3>Webmail Features</h3>



Once logged in to webmail, you can:



<ol><li>**Read Emails**: View your inbox and read messages</li></ol>

<ol><li>**Compose Emails**: Create and send new messages</li></ol>

<ol><li>**Manage Folders**: Organize emails into folders</li></ol>

<ol><li>**Set Filters**: Create rules to automatically sort incoming mail</li></ol>

<ol><li>**Manage Contacts**: Add and organize your contacts</li></ol>



<h2>Email Notifications</h2>



The system sends various email notifications:



<ol><li>**Welcome Emails**: Sent when you first register</li></ol>

<ol><li>**Password Reset**: Sent when you request a password reset</li></ol>

<ol><li>**Account Updates**: Sent when your account information changes</li></ol>

<ol><li>**System Notifications**: Important announcements from administrators</li></ol>



<h3>Managing Notification Preferences</h3>



To manage your email notification preferences:



<ol><li>Go to your Account Settings</li></ol>

<ol><li>Navigate to the "Preferences" or "Notifications" section</li></ol>

<ol><li>Toggle the notification options according to your preferences</li></ol>

<ol><li>Save your changes</li></ol>



<h2>Email Accounts</h2>



As a member, you receive one free email address based on your username. For example, if your username is "john", your email address might be "john@[domain]".



<h3>Email Account Features</h3>



Your email account includes:



<ol><li>**Webmail Access**: Access your email from any web browser</li></ol>

<ol><li>**POP3/IMAP Access**: Configure your desktop or mobile email client</li></ol>

<ol><li>**Spam Filtering**: Basic protection against unwanted emails</li></ol>

<ol><li>**Virus Scanning**: Protection against email-borne threats</li></ol>



<h3>Email Client Configuration</h3>



To set up your email in a desktop or mobile client:



<h4>IMAP Settings (Recommended)</h4>



<ul><li>**Incoming Server**: mail.[domain]</li></ul>

<ul><li>**Port**: 993 (with SSL/TLS)</li></ul>

<ul><li>**Username**: your_username@[domain]</li></ul>

<ul><li>**Password**: your email password</li></ul>



<h4>POP3 Settings</h4>



<ul><li>**Incoming Server**: mail.[domain]</li></ul>

<ul><li>**Port**: 995 (with SSL/TLS)</li></ul>

<ul><li>**Username**: your_username@[domain]</li></ul>

<ul><li>**Password**: your email password</li></ul>



<h4>SMTP Settings (Outgoing Mail)</h4>



<ul><li>**Outgoing Server**: mail.[domain]</li></ul>

<ul><li>**Port**: 587 (with STARTTLS)</li></ul>

<ul><li>**Authentication**: Required</li></ul>

<ul><li>**Username**: your_username@[domain]</li></ul>

<ul><li>**Password**: your email password</li></ul>



<h2>Troubleshooting</h2>



<h3>Common Issues</h3>



<ol><li>**Cannot Access Webmail**</li></ol>

   - Ensure you're using the correct URL

   - Verify your username and password

   - Check if your account is active



<ol><li>**Not Receiving Emails**</li></ol>

   - Check your spam/junk folder

   - Verify your email address is correct in your profile

   - Contact an administrator if the issue persists



<ol><li>**Cannot Send Emails**</li></ol>

   - Verify your outgoing mail settings

   - Check if you've exceeded your sending quota

   - Ensure your account has sending privileges



<h3>Getting Help</h3>



If you encounter issues with your email:



<ol><li>Check the <a href="/Documentation/mail_troubleshooting.md">Mail Troubleshooting Guide</a></li></ol>

<ol><li>Contact your site administrator</li></ol>

<ol><li>Submit a support ticket through the help desk</li></ol>



<h2>Best Practices</h2>



<h3>Security</h3>



<ol><li>**Strong Password**: Use a strong, unique password for your email</li></ol>

<ol><li>**Regular Updates**: Change your password periodically</li></ol>

<ol><li>**Suspicious Emails**: Be cautious of unexpected attachments or links</li></ol>

<ol><li>**Logout**: Always log out when using webmail on shared computers</li></ol>



<h3>Organization</h3>



<ol><li>**Folders**: Create folders to organize different types of emails</li></ol>

<ol><li>**Filters**: Set up filters to automatically sort incoming mail</li></ol>

<ol><li>**Regular Cleanup**: Delete or archive old emails to manage storage</li></ol>



<h3>Etiquette</h3>



<ol><li>**Clear Subject Lines**: Use descriptive subject lines</li></ol>

<ol><li>**Concise Messages**: Keep emails brief and to the point</li></ol>

<ol><li>**Proper Formatting**: Use paragraphs and formatting for readability</li></ol>

<ol><li>**Attachments**: Keep attachments small and use appropriate formats</li></ol>



